This comment has nothing to do with Backbone but we tend to use the sugar syntax for defines:<p>define(function(require){
  var whatever = require('dependency');
});<p>instead of<p>define([
    'dependency',
], function(whatever) {
});<p>We do this because it's way more readable for files with numerous dependencies.<p>Also, we make Backbone, $ and _ globals so we don't have to inject them in every single module.
